    Endoscopy
    Clinical value of alarm features for colorectal cancer. A Meta-Analysis.
When considered independently, alarm features have variable accuracy for CRC, given the high heterogeneity of study populations reflected by wide variability in CRC prevalence. Rectal bleeding and anemia are the most practical to select patients for colonoscopy. Integration of alarm features in a comprehensive evaluation of patient should be considered.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Gastrointest Endosc
    Occurrence of Gastric Cancer in Patients with Juvenile Polyposis Syndrome: A systematic review and meta-analysis. 
The value of GC surveillance in BMPR1A PGV carriers and JPS patients without an identifiable PGV is questionable. Germline testing should be performed in al JPS patients to inform GC risk discussion and utility of surveillance.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 



